article.headline: SE Missouri State 63, Samford 52
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Roy Booker scored 21 points and Terrick Willoughby added 20 to lead Southeast Missouri State past Samford 63-52 Thursday night. The win snapped a 12-game losing streak for the Redhawks (7-19, 4-15 Ohio Valley), and was the 200th victory for Southeast Missouri at the Show Me Center. Samford (17-10, 13-6) came out hot, leading 11-3 at 15:24 after a lay-up by Robert Merritt. But an 18-4 Southeast Missouri run, capped by a Willoughby 3-pointer, gave the Redhawks a 21-15 lead with with 6:12 left in the half. Southeast Missouri led 25-21 at halftime, then used four straight 3-pointers at the start of of the second half to pull away to a 39-26 lead with 17:20 left in the game. Samford closed to within 10 points with 7 minutes left, but that's as close as the Bulldogs could get. Merritt led Samford with 19 points. Paul Paradoski scored 11 points and had five assists for the Redhawks.
